# Security hardening reminder (the demo gate is NOT a real boundary)

The app ships a **B1 demo gate** (see `worker/index.ts` and
`src/components/auth/LoginScreen.tsx`):

- The "Continue as Demo Captain" password is validated **server-side** in the
  Cloudflare Worker (`DEMO_PASSWORD` secret), so it never ships in the bundle.
- BUT the static SPA bundle is public, all demo data is fake/in-bundle, and the
  "signed-in" state is plain client-side React. It gates the **flow**, not the
  **data**, and is trivially bypassable by a technical user. Treat it as a
  speed bump, not security.

## STOP and remind the user before building any of these

Proactively warn the user (don't just start coding) when a request involves:

- Real or **live** data, real brokerage/account **connections** (Webull,
  E*Trade, MooMoo, Plaid, OAuth), API keys, or fetching real market/portfolio
  data.
- Inputting data that resembles a **real person's** account, holdings,
  balances, PII, or credentials — the user's own or anyone else's — even if
  labeled "sample" or "test" data.
- Persisting user data to a real backend or database.

## What to say

> "The current demo gate is cosmetic (B1) — the bundle is public and auth is
> client-side, so it doesn't actually protect data. Before we handle real or
> realistic personal/financial data we should harden: move data behind the
> Worker (cookie-required API), add a real auth provider
> (Supabase/Clerk/Auth0/Cognito) and/or Cloudflare Access, keep secrets
> server-side, and enforce real sessions. Want to do that first?"

Do not silently build real-data features on top of the demo gate.
